Let's go.

125
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:57,167
Yes, Mr. Song. I'll do better this time.

126
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,633
Cue.

127
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:08,867
Mr. Song, I'll go quiet them down.

128
00:08:08,867 --> 00:08:11,233
Wow, what a lovely personality you have.

129
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:13,567
Does it make you laugh?

130
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:17,000
I can't exactly cry, can I?

131
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:19,033
That guy is seriously...

132
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:22,667
He's literally made of annoyance.
Made of pure annoyance.

133
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:24,400
He's just stressed, I guess.

134
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:26,300
Only he's stressed?

135
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:31,033
What even is this for hours now?

136
00:08:31,033 --> 00:08:32,967
They don't even feed us.

137
00:08:32,967 --> 00:08:35,467
Eat something when we go to the market later.

138
00:08:35,467 --> 00:08:37,067
At least, after finishing all the inserts,

139
00:08:37,067 --> 00:08:39,467
it'll probably be bloated noodles or sujebi.

140
00:08:39,467 --> 00:08:43,033
Later, I'll go buy twisted
doughnuts at the market.

141
00:08:43,033 --> 00:08:44,467
Excuse me.

142
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:48,000
My mom used to say that even
a dog bites the one who feeds it.

143
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
But, you've got nothing but a good personality.

144
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,500
That's why PD Song roasts you
whenever there's a chance.

145
00:08:55,567 --> 00:08:58,900
Last year, PD Kang, who worked
with us, was such a great person.

146
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,467
But after the PD changed, this little troublemaker

147
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:04,767
is a complete pain.

148
00:09:04,767 --> 00:09:07,133
I'm fine.

149
00:09:08,167 --> 00:09:10,400
Ah, this...

150
00:09:11,533 --> 00:09:12,567
Here it is.

151
00:09:12,567 --> 00:09:14,367
Ah, this is it?

152
00:09:14,367 --> 00:09:17,300
The new product from our show's sole sponsor.

153
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:18,700
We need to feature this today.

154
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,267
It's on the cue sheet, right?

155
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:21,467
Yes.

156
00:09:21,467 --> 00:09:25,800
We're barely keeping the show
afloat with this production support.

157
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,467
Do well. If you do well...

158
00:09:27,467 --> 00:09:30,867
If you just film one commercial
here, I'll have no regrets.

159
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:31,933
Oh my, oh my.

160
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:33,867
Why waste your wish on something like this?

161
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:37,167
Of course I should. We've been
struggling for five years now.

162
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:41,500
It's better to shoot no
before your skin gets worse.

163
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:43,433
Ah! You scared me.

164
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:46,200
What are you doing?

165
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,100
Filming.

166
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:54,900
Hello.

167
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,667
Just relax and chat with me casually.

168
00:10:03,667 --> 00:10:05,700
Answer my questions, and...

169
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,067
- Oh...
- Yes, just do like that.

170
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:11,000
Yes, alright. Let's do that.

171
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:16,333
Curious what this is?

172
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:19,067
You've been carrying it
around since earlier, right?

173
00:10:19,067 --> 00:10:22,267
Hey, isn't it obvious

174
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:23,833
there's nothing good to salvage
from what we're filming right now?

175
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:25,300
Try just a bit of this.

176
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,600
Leave it to Yeo Reum.

177
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,767
She's been a reporter for five years.

178
00:10:28,767 --> 00:10:31,067
They say you never find what you
need when you're looking for it.

179
00:10:31,067 --> 00:10:33,900
Whenever we look, people never pass by.

180
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,867
This darn travel show...

181
00:10:35,867 --> 00:10:38,933
I should just quit it and walk away. Ugh.

182
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:43,967
Here, try this. I'll give you just a bit.

183
00:10:45,867 --> 00:10:47,467
- Just a bit...
- Just a bit.

184
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:48,700
What's that?

185
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:49,700
This is...

186
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:53,333
This will be really good for
your body once you drink it.

187
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:54,333
Drink it all down.

188
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:57,167
You made this yourself, right?

189
00:10:57,167 --> 00:10:58,467
Ah, of course.

190
00:10:58,467 --> 00:11:00,600
I gathered all the herbs

191
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:03,300
from Myeongbaeksan Mountain over there,

192
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:05,300
and aged them for about five years.

193
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,367
Enzyme, enzyme.

194
00:11:06,367 --> 00:11:09,533
Ah, five-year-aged enzyme.

195
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:13,567
I don't usually show this to others.

196
00:11:13,567 --> 00:11:15,500
No, no. Don't hesitate, just take it.

197
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,033
- Go ahead, drink it all.
- Aren't we supposed to stop them?

198
00:11:17,033 --> 00:11:19,400
What does she think that is, just
accepting and drinking it like that?

199
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,433
Do you think he would give her
something she can't drink?

200
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:22,600
See.

201
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,933
He's so kind and warm.

202
00:11:24,933 --> 00:11:26,067
Don't save it, just drink it straight.

203
00:11:26,067 --> 00:11:28,167
Resident-friendly.

204
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:32,800
I'm not sure if I should be
drinking this precious thing.

205
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:33,900
Good, good.

206
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:37,100
Yeo Reum, just drink it all in one go.

207
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:39,033
All in one shot.

208
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:40,733
Right? One shot.

209
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:45,167
<i>Yeah, it's not like you're
going to die, Kang Yeo Reum.</i>

210
00:11:45,167 --> 00:11:48,533
<i>Drink it quickly and let's wrap up today's shoot.</i>

211
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,167
Then I'll take this precious

212
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:53,500
5-year-aged enzyme, I'll try some.

213
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:58,767
Nice.

214
00:12:00,167 --> 00:12:02,000
Let's get the shot.

215
00:12:03,367 --> 00:12:07,567
Okay, I'll go ahead and start the shot now.

216
00:12:08,433 --> 00:12:10,533
I don't get it, seriously.

217
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:16,833
[Ohkoo Entertainment]

218
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:22,600
Where did you go?

219
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,967
Ah, just take them all off.

220
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:33,033
I poured everything into them...

221
00:12:33,033 --> 00:12:36,733
But kids like that, even when you push
them to the top in supporting or minor roles,

222
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:37,824
they just leave without a second thought.

223
00:12:37,824 --> 00:12:39,033
That's the way kids are these days.

224
00:12:39,033 --> 00:12:41,533
Don't be so harsh.

225
00:12:41,533 --> 00:12:43,333
Our Yeo Reum isn't like that.

226
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,600
Yeo Reum

227
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,867
doesn't have anywhere else to go, that's why.

228
00:12:46,867 --> 00:12:47,900
What's wrong with you?

229
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:50,033
Why are you being so harsh to our star?

230
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:54,433
A company relying on Yeo Reum?
No wonder the ledger's in this state.

231
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,733
